citations.narrative:
The licensee did not use APHIS Forms 7005 and 7006 for three adult dogs that he received on 7/8/25 and have since left.
Not using APHIS forms 7005's and 7006's for all dogs that move in and out of the kennel does not allow for proper
tracking of these dogs by APHIS officials. The licensee must use APHIS Forms 7005 and 7006 for all dogs moving
through the kennel from here on out. Correct starting on 9/29/25.

Six of the adult dogs are not current on their rabies vaccines. In addition, no dogs have been sampled for fecal parasites
in the past year. Not vaccinating all adults dogs for rabies and not sampling the adult dogs for fecal parasites doesn't
ensure the dogs are adequately protected from rabies and the various fecal parasites. All adult dogs must be vaccinated
for rabies and the population must be sampled for fecal parasites in accordance with a plan from the Attending
Veterinarian. Correct by 10/29/25.
This inspection and exit interview were conducted with the licensee.
End of report.
